answers.answer: I was told at one of appointments with my 1st LO that I had some protein in my urine but my doctor didn't seem to concerned just said they would check it again at my next appointment. The next appointment there was no sign of any protein. Just make sure you keep an eye on your BP

question: I am 6 weeks and 2 days and at my appointment today they did a urine and it was positive for protein. They are sending the specimen to the lab and she will call me if it comes back abnormal. Anyone else experience this? Apparently it can be quite common. I don't have any symptoms of a UTI. I'm hoping to wont lead to preeclampsia later on. Thanks!
title: Urine positive for protein?
